               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0097AQG">ʿAddi Qolqʷal Giyorgis / AQG</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1822" notAfter="1828">According to the Addition 1, the Ms.
                        was written in the time of daǧǧāzmāč Sabāgādis Waldu (the ruler of Tǝgray in
                        1822-31), and ʾabuna Qerǝllos (the Metropolitan of Ethiopia in
                        1816-1828).</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>According to Additio 1, the book was bought
                     by Kǝfla Giyorgis with "the money of the church". Kǝfla Giyorgis is mentioned
                     on 10rb, 18ra, 18rb, etc.; the other persons
                     mentioned are Hǝllawe Krǝstos (s. 37vb), Kǝnfa
                     Mikāʾel, Habta Mikāʾel (s. 74rb), Nǝwāya Māryām
                     (s. 74vb), ʾAskāla Māryām (s. 75ra), Walda Gabrǝʾel (s. 78rb).</provenance></history>
